New coercion path [Is_true] : bool >-> Sortclass is ambiguous with existing 
[is_true] : bool >-> Sortclass.
[ambiguous-paths,typechecker]

Section with_signature.
  Context {Σ : Signature}.
  Open Scope ml_scope.
  Open Scope string_scope.
  Open Scope list_scope.

  (*
    Γ ⊢ φ₁ → φ₂
    -------------------- (x ∉ FV(φ₂))
    Γ ⊢ (∃x. φ₁) → φ₂
  *)
  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
ϕ₁, ϕ₂: Pattern
x: evar
i: ProofInfo
pile: ProofInfoLe
  (ExGen := {[x]}, SVSubst := ∅, KT := false,
   FP := ∅) i
x ∉ free_evars ϕ₂
→ Γ ⊢i ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂ using i
  → Γ ⊢i exists_quantify x ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂ using i

ProofInfoMeaning Γ (exists_quantify x ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂)
  (Ex_gen Γ ϕ₁ ϕ₂ x
     (let pf' := pf in
      let pf'0 : well_formed (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) :=
        proved_impl_wf Γ (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) pf' in
      (let H : well_formed ϕ₁ = true :=
         well_formed_imp_proj1 ϕ₁ ϕ₂ pf'0 in
       let H0 : well_formed ϕ₂ = true :=
         well_formed_imp_proj2 ϕ₁ ϕ₂ pf'0 in
       H : well_formed ϕ₁ = true)
        : well_formed ϕ₁)
     (let pf' := pf in
      let pf'0 : well_formed (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) :=
        proved_impl_wf Γ (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) pf' in
      (let H : well_formed ϕ₁ = true :=
         well_formed_imp_proj1 ϕ₁ ϕ₂ pf'0 in
       let H0 : well_formed ϕ₂ = true :=
         well_formed_imp_proj2 ϕ₁ ϕ₂ pf'0 in
       H0 : well_formed ϕ₂ = true)
        : well_formed ϕ₂) pf Hfev) i

    Γ ⊢ φ₁ → φ₂
    -----------------------
    Γ ⊢ (∃x. φ₁) → (∃x. φ₂)
  *)

Hwf: well_formed (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂)
wfϕ₁: well_formed ϕ₁ = true
wfϕ₂: well_formed ϕ₂ = true
Γ ⊢i ?B ---> (ex , ϕ₂^{{evar:x↦0}}) using i

  Defined.

  (*
   Γ ⊢ φ₁ → φ₂
   ----------------------------
   Γ ⊢ φ₁ → ∀x. φ₂
  *)
  (* identity *)
  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
x: evar
P, Q: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
x ∉ free_evars P
→ well_formed_closed_ex_aux P 1
  → Γ ⊢i exists_quantify x P^{evar:0↦x} ---> Q using i
    → Γ ⊢i (ex , P) ---> Q using i

  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
x: evar
P, Q: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
x ∉ free_evars P
→ well_formed_closed_ex_aux P 1
  → Γ ⊢i exists_quantify x P^{evar:0↦x} ---> Q using i
    → Γ ⊢i (ex , P) ---> Q using i

  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
x: evar
P, Q: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
Hx: x ∉ free_evars P
HwfcP: well_formed_closed_ex_aux P 1
H: Γ ⊢i exists_quantify x P^{evar:0↦x} ---> Q using i
Γ ⊢i (ex , P) ---> Q using i

  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
x: evar
P, Q: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
Hx: x ∉ free_evars P
HwfcP: well_formed_closed_ex_aux P 1
H: Γ ⊢i exists_quantify x P^{evar:0↦x} ---> Q using i
((ex , P) ---> Q) =
(exists_quantify x P^{evar:0↦x} ---> Q)

  abstract (
    unfold exists_quantify;
    rewrite -> evar_quantify_evar_open by assumption;
    reflexivity
  ).
  Defined.

  (* identity *)
  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
x: evar
P, Q: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
x ∉ free_evars Q
→ well_formed_closed_ex_aux Q 1
  → Γ ⊢i P ---> exists_quantify x Q^{evar:0↦x} using i
    → Γ ⊢i P ---> (ex , Q) using i

  
Σ: Signature

  (*
    Γ ⊢ ∀x. φ
    ----------
    Γ ⊢ φ
  *)
  
Σ: Signature

ϕ: Pattern
x: evar
i: ProofInfo
well_formed (ex , ϕ)
→ evar_is_fresh_in x ϕ
  → ProofInfoLe
      (ExGen := {[x]}, SVSubst := ∅, KT := false,
       FP := ∅) i
    → Γ ⊢i all , ϕ using i → Γ ⊢i ϕ^{evar:0↦x} using i

  Defined.

  (*
   Γ ⊢ ∀x. (φ₁ → φ₂)
   ------------------
   Γ ⊢ (∃x. φ₁) → φ₂

  When applied backwards,
  turns an existential quantification on the LHS of an implication
  into an universal quantification on top.
  I wonder if we can get an iterative version, saying that
   Γ ⊢ ∀ x. (φ₁ → ... → φᵢ → ... → φₖ → ψ)
   ------------------
   Γ ⊢ φ₁ → ... → (∃x. φᵢ) → ... → φₖ → ψ

  Even better, I would like to have a version which says that
   Γ ⊢ ∀ x₁,...,xₘ,x. (φ₁ → ... → φᵢ → ... → φₖ → ψ)
   ------------------
   Γ ⊢ ∀ x₁,...,xₘ. (φ₁ → ... → (∃x. φᵢ) → ... → φₖ → ψ)

  because that would basically implement [mgDestructEx],
  assuming we hide the leading universal quantifiers.

  TODO: parameterize this lemma with a variable which is fresh in (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂),
  instead of hard-coding the fresh generation.
  *)
  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
ϕ₁, ϕ₂: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
well_formed (ex , ϕ₁)
→ well_formed ϕ₂
  → ProofInfoLe
      (ExGen := {[fresh_evar (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂)]},
       SVSubst := ∅, KT := false, FP := ∅) i
    → Γ ⊢i all , (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) using i
      → Γ ⊢i (ex , ϕ₁) ---> ϕ₂ using i

    → Γ ⊢i all , (ϕ₁ ---> ϕ₂) using i
      → Γ ⊢i (ex , ϕ₁) ---> ϕ₂ using i

  (* Weakening under existential *)
  
Σ: Signature
Γ: Theory
ϕ₁, ϕ₂, ϕ₃: Pattern
i: ProofInfo
well_formed (ex , ϕ₁)
→ well_formed (ex , ϕ₂)
  → well_formed ϕ₃
    → ProofInfoLe
        (ExGen := {[evar_fresh
                      (elements
                         (free_evars ϕ₁
                          ∪ free_evars ϕ₂
                          ∪ free_evars (ex , ϕ₃)))]},
         SVSubst := ∅, KT := false, FP := ∅) i
      → Γ ⊢i all , (ϕ₁ and ϕ₃ ---> ϕ₂) using i
        → Γ ⊢i (ex , ϕ₁) ---> ϕ₃ ---> (ex , ϕ₂)
          using i
